law.text: The results of the election in each county shall be certified by the county election commissioners to the county judge/executive in each county. When more than one (1) county is involved the county judges/executive shall certify the results in their respective counties to the county judge/executive of the county having the largest voting population.
law.history: Amended 1976 (1st Extra. Sess.) Ky. Acts ch. 20, sec. 6, effective January 2, 1978. -- Created 1960 Ky. Acts ch. 114, sec. 21, effective June 16, 1960.
